annotation.TEXT: Of course, it helps if I jump high enough...
Oh, man. The game is telling me to go back, and I think I will this time, because I need to get another Yoshi!
La-lala-lala... Time to blow up the castle!
Um... Uh, oh!
D'oh! The 1-up was indeed there, but I missed it, and instead it gives the bottomless pit an extra life!
Okay, I'm not going to read every single one of these. I don't want to waste all day here when I could be out causing trouble!
That was awesome.
Oh, how I love murdering 8 koopas in cold-blood just to get an extra life for myself!
"Trouble you say? Well, you'd better make it double! To protect the..." No, no. I'm not going to recite the entire Team Rocket motto now. That would just be silly.
Bye... Yoshi? Huh... There was an invisible floor there... Well, I guess that's good, because this level would've been unwinnable without Yoshi if it wasn't there.
Oh! Jackpot! ...But I didn't land back on Yoshi, and now he has to remain stranded in this creepy level forever! (Until I go get him again in another level...)
I think the pipe that's normally around here is missing. And, that gap is way too large to clear from here. But, if I approach this another way...

...Yeah, I get BSoD-ed. Checking back, there are a bunch of pipes lining the floor of that room, but they all crash the game. Also, attempting to open this hack in Lunar Magic doesn't work. That's kind of creepy... Well, I guess that's it for this hack! See ya!
KA-BOOOOMMM!!!

Um, what? I think there are some words missing here. Oh, wait. Is this supposed to be Mad Libs? Okay, maybe it should read, "You get [NOUN] if you cut the [NOUN] at the end. If you collect [NOUN] you can [VERB]."
Huh? Does the fish glitch not work?
And now to go back to go back to go back to go back to go back to mind... games... mind... games...
50-star hits: 1
Uhh... I think the game just crashed. Let me rewind out of this "Black Screen of Death" and start the level over.
Oh, what's this? I guess the overworld events weren't modified. Well, I guess this is the end of the hack. I hope you all enjoyed watching me play MARIO!
Well, there's another pipe, but...
No Yoshi, because he's too creeped out by this pasta.
Hello, and welcome back to MARIO, a creepypasta production! Let's see how stripped down Yoshi's Island 3... er, I mean 7 is...
Space-time rewind count: 1
Wait, you're not implying that I--
Yay, happy music!
Oh, another hidden pipe! I should've guessed.
Maybe there's another hidden pipe in this room that I have to find...
I can't jump over this wall...
Gotta check every cement block...
And, let me guess. I have to find another hidden pipe in this room?
It is! And he's dead within 5 seconds, just like that!
Demo count: 1?
Oh, maybe I was slurping up the P-switch too quickly the first couple of times.
Death music and two message boxes. Um...
Oh, it's that invisible floor from "leave now". Thanks for saving my life again, man!
Huh? There's... nothing here?
Okay, so let's not enter that invisible pipe at the start this time...
Okay, so for some reason, half of these message boxes are blank except for Yoshi's signature, while the other half secretly wants me to cause more trouble, mwahaha!
Okay, that definitely counts as solid proof!
...Um... game?
Also, bonus game.
Maybe there are more invisible floors around here, but I don't want to take a chance without solid proof.
Just to be sure, this level's unmodified, right?
Okay, so we've got upside-down boiling cement that I can safely swim in the bottom row of, and a bunch of message boxes.
Was that maybe a placeholder level, or is this game trying to creep me out?
So, I guess I'll just listen to this awesome castle music while I steadily advance forward at this arbitrarily slow automatic screen-scrolling speed set by Nintendo...
Oh... dear... That's, uh... Ugh... That's not pleasant-sounding at all... Wow, that's really gruesome... Who could've done such a horrific thing?
Nuts. Nothing... Maybe there's more to this room?
I can see a couple coins up there, but I can't get past this invisible wall...
Umm... I might very well be stuck...
Oh, it's a boss door! Is it Iggy?
Well, let's see what's up ahead...
Aha! Found it! Now, what's next?
Well, if the super koopas are still here, I should certainly be able to get a cape...
Okay, this almost looks like Yoshi's Island 4, but there's no water, no fish, and spooky music. Hey, I wonder if that 1-up is still up there?
Well, that was a short level.
What? I can't "leave now"! I'm just getting started!
Yeah, I'd love to "Fly away", if I could just get the first super koopa to spawn (assuming it's even still there)...
Hi, Yoshi!
The game won't let me enter these doors in my current state, right?
What the? An invisible pipe?
I wonder what's going on around here...

Okay, so the game force-fed me a mushroom upon entering this room, and then presents me with doors that only a small plumber could fit through. Hmm... This must be a puzzle room, and I've got to find a way to injure myself.
Ha! I can certainly clear those gaps from up here!
Oh, but there's an invisible wall in my way...
What? A dead end? But... Then, what do I do?
The P-switch and star are still present, but... It doesn't appear that there's much I can do with them...
